boost
------------------------------------------
Boost provides free peer-reviewed portable C++ source libraries.

We emphasize libraries that work well with the C++ Standard Library. 
Boost libraries are intended to be widely useful, and usable across a 
broad spectrum of applications. The Boost license encourages both 
commercial and non-commercial use.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.0-60
  libbz2_1-1.0.5-10
  libgcc1-4.3.2-2
  libicu38-3.8-5
  libstdc++6-4.3.2-2
  python-2.5.4-10
  zlib0-1.2.3-10

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.19.51-1
  cmake-2.6.4-10
  cygport-0.9.9-1
  gcc4-core-4.3.2-2
  gcc4-g++-4.3.2-2
  make-3.81-2

Canonical website:
  http://www.boost.org/

Canonical download:
  http://downloads.sourceforge.net/boost/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack boost-1.40.0-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./boost-1.40.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/boost-1.40.0-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libboost-devel-1.40.0-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libboost1.40-1.40.0-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

